definition: containing nothing, an empty area or space, excrete or discharge from the body
details:
adjective
- containing nothing
= example: containing nothing
- lacking any legal or binding force
= example: lacking any legal or binding force
= synonyms: null
noun
- an empty area or space
= example: an empty area or space
= synonyms: vacuum, emptiness, vacancy
- the state of nonexistence
= synonyms: nullity, nothingness, nihility
verb
- excrete or discharge from the body
= synonyms: empty
- take away the legal force of or render ineffective
= synonyms: invalidate
- clear (a room, house, place) of occupants or empty or clear (a place or receptacle) of something
= example: clear (a room, house, place) of occupants or empty or clear (a place or receptacle) of something
- declare invalid
= synonyms: invalidate, nullify, annul, quash
